<div id="c13">
<p>PJ, &#8220;survival of the fittest&#8221; is a tautology. Who survives? The fittest. Who are the fittest? Those that survive. In reality, who survives involves a great deal of randomness.</p>

<p>In any event, the fact that Bach&#8217;s music survived while that of his contemporaries didn&#8217;t may mean that Bach&#8217;s music was better, but I don&#8217;t see how it can mean that it&#8217;s better than today&#8217;s music, which hasn&#8217;t exactly died out yet.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a rel="nofollow" href="../index.html">Aaron Swartz</a>
