<div id="c52">
<p>Aaron, I am sure even Aimee Mann or Britney Spears are standing on the shoulders of giants like Mozart and Bach. They may or may not know it&#8230;but all music today is a mutation(as in genetic mutation) from classical music. Of course, some of the genes are introduced from Africa, Asia Pacific, Middle East etc. You can&#8217;t (fairly) dismiss or diss the genes and still like the result. For instance, many of us are the result of intermarriages between settlers, immigrants and such. Tiger Woods or Keanu Reeves will not appreciate being told that you are OK with part of their genes, but don&#8217;t appreciate the rest.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.ticketnest.com">Heidi</a>
